data.description: This spacious 4-bedroom, 2.5-bathroom home is in the Mckewn neighborhood, within the highly regarded DD2 school district, and offers a perfect blend of comfort, style, and convenience. Upon entering this home, you'll immediately notice the open and inviting layout. The spacious living areas are designed for both relaxation and entertaining and the heart of the home is the kitchen which features granite countertops, an oversized island, stainless steel appliances, and a bright, open design. Sliding doors provide seamless access to the backyard, making outdoor dining and entertaining a breeze. The backyard is fully fenced for privacy and security, offering a spacious patio area and a charming fire pit - an ideal setting for enjoying the beautiful South Carolina evenings. Upstairs, you'llfind all four bedrooms, providing plenty of space for your family and guests. The master bedroom is a true retreat, featuring two closets and a generously sized ensuite bathroom with large walk-in shower. This home also includes the convenience of an attached 2-car garage and fully paid off solar panels, lowering your energy costs! Living in the Mckewn neighborhood means you'll have access to fantastic community amenities, including an incredible pool, playground, pickle ball and bocce ball courts perfect for staying active and socializing with neighbors.
